item.title: AI Images Create Confusion as Real Gang of Monkeys Roams St. Louis
item.description: Police have patrolled the area based on reports of sightings, but the monkeys still haven't been found.

item.title: More than 100 new tech unicorns were minted in 2025 — here they are
item.description: Using data from Crunchbase and PitchBook, TechCrunch tracked down the VC-backed startups that became unicorns so far this year.

item.title: These super cheap noise-cancelling headphones boast a 110-hour battery, but I still can't recommend them — here's why
item.description: I tested these ultra-cheap noise cancelling headphones from Tribit, and they prove that a low price doesn’t mean you’re getting high value for money.

item.title: Tracking Insider Trading on Polymarket Is Turning Into a Business of Its Own
item.description: Insider trading on prediction markets is lucrative. Finding and copying said insider trading, also.

item.title: New Proposed Legislation Would Let Self-Driving Cars Operate in New York State
item.description: New York governor Kathy Hochul says she will propose a new law allowing limited autonomous vehicle pilots in smaller cities. Full-blown services could be next.

item.title: The best robot vacuums we’ve tested for 2026
item.description: Robot vacuums are impressive devices that will clean your floors well and — thanks to bigger batteries and better robot brains — rarely get tired of doing their job. item.title: OpenAI buys tiny health records startup Torch for, reportedly, $100M
item.description: AI health records startup Torch will be using its tech for OpenAI's new ChatGPT Health, according to co-founder Ilya Abyzov.
